      <p>If I could give a new producer one sentence, it's this: your job is to be the person for whom the film getting made is a personal, non-negotiable responsibility. Not the most talented person, not the richest, not the loudest — the one who takes ownership when nobody else will, who plans for the problem, stays calm through it, looks after the people, and drags the thing across the finish line when everyone else has run out of steam. Every other skill in this course serves that one stance. Decide the film is yours to make happen, and you're already most of the way to being a producer.</p>
